<item>
            <title>[WFLY-1929] TransactionalInterceptorBase doesn&apos;t implement Serializable</title>
                <link>https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-1929</link>
                <project id="12313721" key="WFLY">WildFly</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I just downloaded the latest WildFly snapshot which contains an upgrade of IronJacamar. The annotation @Transactional works fine for @RequestScoped requests (see &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.jboss.org/browse/WFLY-1496&quot; title=&quot;@Transactional doesn&amp;#39;t work&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;WFLY-1496&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;WFLY-1496&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, if I&apos;m using @SessionScoped for CDI beans in a JSF-based web application, then I get the stacktrace below. The solution is pretty simple:&lt;br/&gt;
The interceptor class TransactionalInterceptorBase in Narayana&apos;s package com.arjuna.ats.jta.cdi.transactional has to implement the interface java.io.Serializable.&lt;/p&gt;

